dfischer.utils

Class LoadtestExternalLocalResourcesDataRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.LoadtestExternalLocalResourcesDataRecord

  • public class LoadtestExternalLocalResourcesDataRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    Definition of an additional, external resource that is available on the local system, and must be transferred to the load generator (Exec Agent) when executing a load test job. Typically such an external resource is a Java library file (*.jar file) which is used by a plug-in. However, also any other file type can be transferred.
    See Also:
    LoadtestExternalResources

      • LoadtestExternalLocalResourcesDataRecord

        public LoadtestExternalLocalResourcesDataRecord(long localResourceId,
                                        java.lang.String localFilePath,
                                        boolean addToClassPath,
                                        boolean addToXbootclasspath)
        Create a new instance an initialize the instance with the data of a local file that will be transferred to the load generator (Exec Agent). Note: the resource type is implicitely configured to the value LOCAL_RESOURCE_TYPE_FILE.
        Parameters:
        localResourceId - unique ID that is assigned to the instance
        localFilePath - absolute path to the local file
        addToClassPath - if set to true: add the file to the Java CLASSPATH on the load generator when executing a load test job
        addToXbootclasspath - if set to true: add the file to the Java -Xbootclasspath/p: on the load generator when executing a load test job
        See Also:
        LOCAL_RESOURCE_TYPE_FILE
